fields.name: Oompah Brass
fields.biography:
Oompah Brass is a critically acclaimed Brass ensemble and the world’s leading exponents of ‘Oom-pop’!

Described by Chris Evans as ‘legends in lederhosen’! 

Formed by some of the UK’s most versatile brass players, Oompah Brass started out with the firm intention of becoming a traditional German Oompah Band.

However, they quickly realised that novel arrangements of pop tunes carried more appeal than the waltzes, polkas and marches more commonly associated with the genre.

Oompah Brass are now a multiple award-winning, critically acclaimed brass ensemble and are the world’s leading exponents of ‘Oom-pop’ – Bavarian style re-workings of songs such as Paradise City, Toxic and Bohemian Rhapsody to mention just a few.

The five pioneers of Oom-pop feature two Trumpets, Horn, Trombone and Tuba and have performed in iconic venues such as the Montreux Palace Hotel in Switzerland, the Hammersmith Apollo and the London Olympic Stadium!

Oompah Brass are equally at home playing in front of any size of audience large or small and any type of event – an absolute must hear!

fields.name: The Gemini Duo
fields.biography:
The Gems met when studying for their BMus (Hons) Music Degree at Trinity College of Music, London.

They formed The Gems Duo, a vibrant and dynamic ensemble, providing both Classical, Latin and Popular Music, along with a touch of style to any event.

The Gems Duo combines the flourishing sound of flute with the depth and mellow tones of the cello, creating a unique and elegant partnership. The duo have performed all over the UK, tailoring their repertoire and adding a touch of class to every function.

The Gems Duo welcome requests for music for every occasion.

fields.name: Felice Cello Duo
fields.biography:
Felice Cello Duo came about when Jenny and Leah met in 2007 in the picturesque hill-top town of Montepulciano, Italy. On discovering how well the sound of their two cellos worked together, the pair decided to find a way to work together more often.

Felice Cello Duo believe that every event is unique, and are more than happy to discuss specific music requests and arrange any music for your special event.

fields.name: The Royal Union
fields.biography:
The Royal Union is one of the most sought after acts in the U.K. with a unique energy, style and charisma that will leave the audience screaming for more. Comfortable performing for 100- 100,000 people on some of the most prestigious stages in the world including London’s very own Wembley Arena and Royal Albert Hall. This 3 or 4 piece is a band, a stage show, a concert experience! 
 
Piloted by experienced frontman Craig and backed by the UK’s Finest session musicians this small band has a massive sound. With rich, thick harmonies that are ‘off the clock’ brilliant, a huge 500 song repertoire and a variety of separate vocalists, giving them the ability to choose the right singer for the right song, this un-rivalled live band re- create the original versions closer than any other act around. 

Bandoke

If you’re after something different, off the wall and unique why not try Bandeoke - karaoke on steroids. Bandeoke or live band karaoke gives you the unique opportunity to sing with one of the UK’s most popular party bands live on stage. Simply choose a song from the bands extensive repertoire and we will have all the words, microphones and air guitars ready for you to give the performance of your life. Rock out with this growing craze and bring the house down as Madonna, Elvis or Amy Winehouse, the stage in yours!

fields.name: DJ Paige
fields.biography:
Create memorable moments with London Sound Academy Graduate - DJ Paige. Paige is an enthusiastic Multi-Genre London based DJ who mixes a variety of genres ranging from Motown, Disco, Chart, House, Hip Hop/Rnb, Garage, Drum and Bass, 80s, Reggaeton and more.

Paige spent 2018-2019 being a freelance supporting DJ who performed at numerous venues around the UK such as: Heaton House Farm, Hartsfield Manor, Cherwell Boat House, Wadhurst Castle, Brookfield Barn, Micklefield Hall, Moxhull Hall, Devonport House, The Mount Vineyard and more.

Paige enrolled into LSA (London Sound Academy) in 2019 to advance her DJing skills set. Since joining LSA, her mixes have been recognised within the DJ scene, which has led to multiple radio stations approaching her to be a Guest DJ on their shows. Her first ever guest mix was for Mini Radio Belgium (2020) and she was also offered a residency with Quest London Radio, “Fusion Fridayz." Paige’s biggest achievement with radio so far was being approached by 4 different artists - Dipz Mistry, Kruel Intentions, Nüwa Nrth & Rick Sanchez - she was asked to feature on their radio shows on Data Transmission (where she played on the same line up as Roger Sanchez). Select Radio & Foundation FM. This was done over a 4 week period from the 11th June- 1st July 2021. Paige has worldwide listeners tuning into her mixes - France, Belgium, Spain, Poland, Germany, Mexico, Brazil, Jamaica & Japan - all sets can be found on Soundcloud: DJ Paige Renée.

fields.name: DJ Danny
fields.biography:
DJ Danny is the ultimate party DJ!

Danny's interests run the full spectrum of a wide selection of genres of music and with over 10 years of experience, he's a seasoned DJ who covers all events Including Birthdays, Weddings, School Proms, Corporate and End of year events.

Professional services provided, punctual and loves the job at hand no matter how big or small. DJ Danny combines special effect lighting to create that perfect party atmosphere, with an excellent ability to read the crowd to make your event one to remember.

fields.name: DJ Knight
fields.biography:
DJ KNIGHT is an international open format DJ & MC playing in the UK and globally                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             He has extensive experience and knowledge of special events & entertainment.

DJ KNIGHT specialises in playing at commercial, corporate, private & special events such as: Award ceremonies, Bar / Bat Mitzvah's, Corporate functions, Gala dinners, Milestone birthdays, Product launches, & Luxury weddings.

He works closely with clients to ensure they hear the music they want. This personal approach has made DJ Knight a sought after professional for events in the UK & globally.

His vast knowledge of music allows him to play all types of music such as 60,70,80,00's, funk, blues, soul, commercial, pop, R&B, Hip-hop, house & garage, dancehall and dance floor classics.

Corporate clients include: Barclaycard, Mishcon de Reya, Virgin Atlantic, Delta, Heineken, BSKYB, Panasonic.

fields.name: DJ Gerard
fields.biography:
DJ Gerard is a highly sought after professional DJ with 20 years of experience playing at top events around the world.  These include residencies at The Ministry of Sound, The Wimbledon Tennis Tournament and The Emirates Stadium with prestigious corporate clients to include VW, Westons Cider, H&M and New Look Men.

DJ Gerard has so much passion for music and this is reflected by his floor-filling, high energy DJ'ing style together with a huge repertoire of over 15,000 songs to cater for any event.

If you are looking to avoid the 'traditional wedding DJ' and enjoy music professionally mixed with songs carefully selected on crowd reaction then look no further!  Gerard is also happy to provide a bespoke song list, in which the client can work closely with him to ensure that their tastes are catered for and truly compliment the event requirements.

fields.name: Cutting Edge Big Band
fields.biography:
The Cutting Edge Big Band has a stylish and exciting sound: beautiful melodies and joyously toe-tapping rhythms from serious musicians who love playing. 

Whether wistful ballads or stomping dance numbers, this is classy entertainment in a variety of settings, with a set list tailored to every event. 

The repertoire is rooted in the classic swing era of the ‘30s and ‘40s.  Those days of romance: glamour, moonshine and tuxedos, the excitement of Harlem and invention of wild, new dance crazes.  Think wartime tunes made famous by Duke Ellington, Count Basie, Ella Fitzgerald and Glenn Miller. 

Then there are the mid-century classics that everyone knows - Frank Sinatra, Doris Day, Dean Martin; and even the occasional tune from Stevie Wonder, the Beatles, Billy Joel, or the achingly cool Astrud Gilberto.  Great melodies that have been sung by everyone from Rod Stewart to Michael Buble to Robbie Williams … 

The Cutting Edge Big Band has been performing around Oxford since 1982 and is now led by Chris Macklow, a man of easy vintage charm and smooth sophistication. His apparently laid-back style hides a ruthless attention to detail.

fields.name: Hipster
fields.biography:
Hipster have performed at many prestigious venues over the years including: The Grosvenor Hotel, The Savoy Hotel, The Natural History Museum, Manchester Town Hall, The Royal Courts of Justice, Eltham Palace, Kensington Roof Gardens, Euro Disney, Kew Gardens, Bath Assembly Rooms, Manchester Art Gallery, The Grand Hotel Brighton plus numerous Awards ceremonies including IVCA, HFMA, Wella, Trend Vision Awards and NABS. The last 6 years have seen the boys working along side numerous celebrities including T4 presenter Steve Jones, impressionist Rory Bremner, comedian Lenny Henry, legendary record producer Nick Lowe and BBC Radio 2's Jeremey Vine amongst others.

Their current corporate clients include Channel 5, Marks and Spencer, Hewlett Packard, Zafer Associates, Oxford University Press, NSPCC, Royal Bank of Scotland, Barclays and Natwest - to name a few!!

Internationally, Hipster have performed in Singapore, Dubai, Potugal, Spain, France and Austria.

fields.name: Railroad Kin
fields.biography:
Railroad Kin are a charming and energetic acoustic folk band, whose foot-stomping sets are guaranteed to have everyone jumping onto the dance floor.

Every Railroad Kin performance is jam-packed with feel-good flair, plus music and vocals from some of the UK's finest musicians. The band are experts at getting crowds up and dancing, with each set filled with incomparable energy and audience interaction.

This fabulous, folky 6-piece is comprised of spectacular male vocals, sizzling saxophone, guitar, bass, keys and rhythmic drums. Railroad Kin have a wealth of experience, performing for over 600 happy couples in the last 7 years. Whilst studying music at university together, they formed close-knit friendships and a brotherly bond, which is reflected in their charismatic and care-free vibe when they set foot on stage.

Although vastly experienced as a band, each member is an equally experienced musician in their own right. Individually, they have toured with the likes of Ed Sheeran, Rag'n'Bone Man and Bastille. Members of the band also performed at the Olympic 2012 closing ceremony and toured extensively in the UK, Europe and the Americas.

With a varied repertoire that ranges from 60's rock n roll all the way through to the latest contemporary hits, flavoured with their signature folky-style twist, Railroad Kin's sets have a little bit of everything, and something for everyone.

fields.title: the dos and don'ts of choosing wedding ceremony music
fields.content:
The build up to your walk down the aisle is enormous. For many brides, the moment they step down the aisle is the moment their wedding really starts, it’s what everything has been building towards, and so it’s only natural that you want it to be nothing short of perfect. Getting your wedding ceremony music right will play a big part in this, so here are the dos and don’ts you need to get it just right.

DO set the mood
You don’t need us to tell you that your wedding day will be emotional and romantic. Just as you’ll likely choose a song that is filled with these emotions for your first dance, do the same for your wedding ceremony music. It can be instrumental, but it does need to enhance all those magical things you’ll be feeling as you walk down the aisle to your future husband or wife!

DON’T feel like you have to stay traditional
While a pianist or organist might be tradition (and very beautiful), they aren’t your only options. Other live musicians to consider are harpists, soul choirs or even a live band. Don’t discount recorded music, either, just make sure the songs you choose are appropriate in lyrics and length.

DO make it ambient
Whatever wedding ceremony music you choose, make sure it’s ambient and comfortable for listeners. Consider the volume – you don’t want anything too loud – and make sure the pace is slow and calming. This will help keep your groom relaxed and give you a natural rhythm to match as you walk down the aisle towards him.

 

DON’T make a last minute decision
The song you just absolutely fell for on the radio last week might seem like the perfect choice, but stop and really think about it before you choose it for your wedding day. How often do trendy songs come and go? How often do you listen to them so many times you fall out of love with them? You don’t want this to be how you remember your wedding ceremony, so approach the latest tunes with care and try not to make a last minute decision if you can help it.

DON’T forget to pick a song for your walk out, too
So far, all we’ve been thinking about is what music you will walk down the aisle to, but what about when you exit the church as newlyweds, otherwise known as your recessional music? Make sure you choose a musical accompaniment for this too, it’ll be the first walk you take as a married couple so you want it to be atmospheric and memorable.
fields.author: Lauren Fraser

fields.title: choosing a live band for your wedding
fields.content:
Are you considering a band at your wedding? It all sounds so simple until you realise just how varied they can be. We’ve rounded up the best advice to help you when choosing a live band.

Choosing a Band for Your Wedding
Why have a band?

Depending on the length of your reception, you may not want a DJ for the whole of it. A live band adds a certain level of interaction and engagement that draws out the best in people. Throwing a band into the mix breaks up the evening with a little more action.

“Live music from good musicians has an infectious enthusiasm, especially at such a happy occasion,” Says Charlie Talbot, manager of Oompah Brass.

What type of band?

Whether you want a stationary or roaming band will add time to your search. Roaming bands are harder to come by but all the more entertaining because of their crowd engagement. You’re more likely to find a New Orleans style brass band or a Bavarian brass band, such as Oompah Brass who roam as they perform.

Brass bands, in particular, are louder and more impactful acoustically. As a result, you may not have to require a PA system to amplify the sound of your band (unless you’ve got over 200+ guests).

What about the appearance? 

It depends if you want your band to blend into the background or to stand out and really entertain. With a brass band, not only does the music entertain but the instruments with their florid designs and shapes can really add to the show.

What type of music?

There’s a whole world of various bands out there to choose from. From soul to jazz, brass to basic cover bands, it’s safe to say we’re spoilt for choice. You need to think about the percussion and style you like most before filtering through bands and sending endless enquiries.

When do you book the band for?

Bands are most commonly booked for the reception, to really kickstart the party and get guests up on their feet. Pull together a playlist of songs that are sure to have your guests busting a move and the band will make the magic happen.

Charlie Talbot, tells us of the different and varied options for when to introduce the band (particularly great if they’re a roaming brass):

“Processing between the ceremony and reception venue, being followed down the street by all the guests,” he says and we can’t help but imagine what a great wedding photo that will be.

“Playing fanfares as guests clutch their first glass of champagne, playing background music during receptions and… keeping a dance floor jumping long into the small hours”. 

How much should you budget?

There’s usually a minimum performance time of an hour but typically people tend to book for a couple of hours before a DJ. We would recommend you budget from £800 – £3,000 for a live band. The greater the number of instruments, the greater the cost.

How far in advance should I book?

As soon as possible, the wedding season is a busy time for musicians.

“As with venues, caterers and everything else, the sooner you book, the more relaxed you can be. Summer weekends get booked up quickly so you need to know the availability of your options a long way in advance,” Says Charlie.
fields.author: Kelly Greene
